 :tx/rationale "ARCHITECTURAL PRIMITIVE: THE EPISTEMOLOGICAL TRIANGLE. Three irreducible operations underlie all knowledge in the store: (1) ASSERTION (monadic) — how knowledge enters. observe: Reality → Store(Datom). Wraps reality fragment in provenance context. (2) FALSIFICATION (comonadic) — how knowledge is tested. challenge: Store(H) → (H, {¬Hᵢ}). Embeds hypothesis in refutation context. The comonadic duplicate generates the dialectical tree: falsifications of falsifications, converging to fixed point. (3) WITNESS (constructive bridge) — how survival becomes knowledge. witness: ¬¬H → H. Provides the constructive evidence that turns 'not yet falsified' into 'verified with evidence'. Every datom exists in triple context: how it entered (provenance), how it could be destroyed (falsification set), why it survived (witness). A datom with only (1) is OPINION. With (1)+(2) it is HYPOTHESIS. With (1)+(2)+(3) it is KNOWLEDGE. F(S) should weight by epistemic status: opinions contribute nothing, knowledge contributes fully. The coKleisli arrows of the Dialectical Comonad ARE the challenge protocol steps. The monad-comonad adjunction IS the observation-projection duality. The constructive bridge IS the FBW system. Everything we built maps to this triangle."
